{"id":3213,"date":"2022-11-01T13:23:02","date_gmt":"2022-11-01T13:23:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/zcmpsandbox.com\/?page_id=3213"},"modified":"2023-08-25T17:30:31","modified_gmt":"2023-08-25T17:30:31","slug":"towards-an-exhibition","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/towards-an-exhibition\/","title":{"rendered":"Towards an Exhibition"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-medium-font-size\"><em>I\u015f\u0131n \u00d6nol and Aya Labanieh <\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"105\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/line4-1024x105.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4396\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/line4-1024x105.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/line4-300x31.jpg 300w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/line4-768x79.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/line4-1536x157.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/line4-2048x210.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/line4-2000x205.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-2 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Small groups of participants worked together to think about how the individual and group projects on loss could be amplified and transformed with an eye to the Imagine Repair exhibition. This workshop allowed us to think about curation, and about how our work with memory, justice, and repair could be shaped to reach a larger public. How can the transformative power of art mobilize our memories in the interest of justice and repair?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Unfolding over the course of several days, with sessions held in-person at the Cathedral of St. John the Divine and on Zoom for those who could not attend, the workshop solicited the passionate ideas and interests of over twenty-two community participants and local artists.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/ZCMP_towards_an_exhbition.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"402\" height=\"89\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/TOOLKIT2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3910\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/TOOLKIT2.jpg 402w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/TOOLKIT2-300x66.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" \/><\/a><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1001\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/toward-an-exhition-1001x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4333\" srcset=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/toward-an-exhition-1001x1024.jpg 1001w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/toward-an-exhition-293x300.jpg 293w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/toward-an-exhition-768x785.jpg 768w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/toward-an-exhition-1502x1536.jpg 1502w, https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/toward-an-exhition.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1001px) 100vw, 1001px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-small-font-size\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/zcmp.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/cam-1.jpg\">  <em>Header photo: Aya Labanieh<\/em><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I\u015f\u0131n \u00d6nol and Aya Labanieh Small groups of participants worked together to think about how the individual and group projects on loss could be amplified and transfor